<p>I have an Xceed datagrid control: </p>  <pre><code>public partial class ExtendedDataGridControl : DataGridControl, INotifyPropertyChanged {...} </code></pre>  <p>In the constructor I subscribe for an event:</p>  <pre><code>EventManager.RegisterClassHandler(typeof(DataRow), DataRow.MouseDoubleClickEvent, new MouseButtonEventHandler(OnDataRowMouseDoubleClick)); </code></pre>  <p>But I don't know how to unsubsribe. I have tried </p>  <pre><code>this.MouseDoubleClick -= OnDataRowMouseDoubleClick; this.RemoveHandler(DataRow.MouseDoubleClickEvent, new MouseButtonEventHandler(OnDataRowMouseDoubleClick)); DataRowMouseDoubleClick = null; </code></pre>  <p>But I guess it is still not working, since windows which contain the <code>ExtendedGatagridControl</code> are never collected by GC.</p>  <p>I can't move the subscribtion to the static constructor because the event fires on every instance so I have to check which one was clicked.</p>  <pre><code> private void OnDataRowMouseDoubleClick(object sender, MouseButtonEventArgs e)  {      DataRow row = sender as DataRow;      ExtendedDataGridControl grid = DataGridControl.GetDataGridContext(row).DataGridControl as ExtendedDataGridControl;         //ExtendedDataGridControl grid = row.GetVisualParent&lt;ExtendedDataGridControl&gt;();       if (row != null &amp;&amp; DataRowMouseDoubleClick != null &amp;&amp; grid == this)      {          DataRowMouseDoubleClick(row);      } } </code></pre>  <p>So how can I unsubscribe from the event ?</p>